Here is a simple C++ program that reads a text file line by line and counts the number of occurrences of a specific word in the file:

```c++
#include <iostream>
#include <fstream>
using namespace std;

int main() {
    // Declare variables
    int count = 0;
    std::ifstream inputFile("textfile.txt");
    if (inputFile) {
        while (inputFile.good()) {
            std::string line;
            // Read a line from the file
            inputFile >> line;
            // Check if the word is in the line
            if (line.find("word") != std::string::npos) {
                // Increase the count by 1
                count++;
            }
        }
        // Close the file
        inputFile.close();
    }
    // Display the count
    cout << "There are " << count << " occurrences of the word \"word\" in the text file." << endl;
}
```

This program opens the text file "textfile.txt" and reads each line of the file. It then checks to see if the word "word" is in the line and increases the count by 1. After all lines have been processed, the program displays the count of occurrences of the word "word" in the text file.
